    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-07-13T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-07-13T01:00:00-05:00" n="691"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d691">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.6363/31: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-13T09:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 13, 1942—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1221. General Maxwell<note n="37" xml:id="d691fn37">Maj. Gen. Russell L. Maxwell,
                        in command of American Forces in the Middle East with headquarters at
                        Cairo.</note> informs me that he has suggested to War Department that
                    General Spalding<note n="38" xml:id="d691fn38">Brig. Gen. Sidney P.
                        Spalding.</note> who is proceeding to this area be requested to cause a
                    survey to be made of possible defense and denial measures applicable to the oil
                    companies at Bahrein and in Saudi Arabia which have recently been the subject of
                    an informal investigation by Lieutenant Commander Lockard, United States Naval
                    Observer at Basra.</p>
                <p>As Department is aware this question has been the subject of messages from this
                    Legation and the Legation at Jidda and in view of fact that any action along
                    this line may involve presence in Saudi Arabia of American experts I urge that
                    Moose be kept informed of developments in order that he may be in position to
                    give advice and recommend measures with a view to minimizing danger of arousing
                    Saudi Arabian susceptibilities at this time.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Jidda.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
